# CertifyMe Full Stack Assessment

## Project Overview

This project is a Full Stack Admin Portal developed as part of the CertifyMe Full Stack Intern Technical Assessment.
The application provides secure admin authentication and opportunity management with complete backend implementation using Flask and SQLite.

---

# Tech Stack

## Backend

- Python
- Flask
- SQLite

## Frontend

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

---

# Features

## Authentication

- Admin Signup
- Admin Login
- Forgot Password (Token-based Reset)
- Session-based Authentication
- Secure Logout

## Opportunity Management

- Create Opportunities
- View Opportunities
- Edit Opportunities
- Delete Opportunities

## Security & Validation

- Email format validation
- Minimum password length validation
- Session authentication
- User-specific data isolation
- Password reset token expiry (1 hour)

---

# API Endpoints

## Authentication APIs

| Method | Endpoint                    | Description                   |
| ------ | --------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| POST   | `/api/auth/signup`          | Register new admin            |
| POST   | `/api/auth/login`           | Login admin                   |
| POST   | `/api/auth/forgot-password` | Generate password reset token |
| GET    | `/api/auth/me`              | Get logged-in admin details   |
| POST   | `/api/auth/logout`          | Logout admin                  |

---

## Opportunity APIs (Authenticated)

| Method | Endpoint                  | Description            |
| ------ | ------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| GET    | `/api/opportunities`      | Get all opportunities  |
| GET    | `/api/opportunities/<id>` | Get single opportunity |
| POST   | `/api/opportunities`      | Create opportunity     |
| PUT    | `/api/opportunities/<id>` | Update opportunity     |
| DELETE | `/api/opportunities/<id>` | Delete opportunity     |

---

# Backend Implementation Status

Implemented with:

- Proper REST API structure
- HTTP status codes
- JSON responses
- Authentication validation
- Data persistence using SQLite
- User-specific access control
- CORS support for frontend integration

